│ nsw i8 0, %X`, which is `-X`.\n\nLet's test the failing case from the log: `%X = -1`.\n-   │
│ **Source**:\n  - `%BO1 = -1 * -128 = 128`, which wraps to `-128` in `i8`.\n  - `%BO0 = -1  │
│ * 127 = -127`.\n  - `%r = srem i8 -128, -127`. The result of `srem a, b` is `a - (a/b)*b`. │
│ Here, `(-128) / (-127)` is `1`. So, `%r = -128 - (1 * -127) = -128 + 127 = -1`.\n-         │
