│ `InstructionSimplify` library.                                                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ My initial analysis correctly identified `InstCombineMulDivRem.cpp` as the source of the   │
│ bug, but I was unable to locate the specific code block. After re-examining the file, I    │
│ have found the relevant logic. The transformation for `srem (X * C), (X * (C+1))` was      │
│ missing a special case for when `C` is the minimum signed value.                           │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will now add the correct special case to `InstCombineMulDivRem.cpp`. This is the same    │
│ logic I tried to add to `InstructionSimplify.cpp`, but in the correct location this time.  │
│                                                                                            │
│ First, I will revert the incorrect change I made.                                          │
│ <tool_call>                                                                                │
│ {                                                                                          │
│   "name": "reset",                                                                         │
│   "args": {                                                                                │
